{{Primary sources|date=May 2011}} {{Infobox book | name = Highest Duty: My Search for What Really Matters | image = highestduty.jpg | author = [[Chesley Sullenberger]], [[Jeffrey Zaslow]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | series = | genre = [[memoir]] | publisher = [[William Morrow and Company|William Morrow]] | release_date = 2009 | media_type = Print (hardback & paperback) | pages = 352 pp. | isbn = 978-0-06-192468-2 | oclc = 435730624 | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''Highest Duty: My Search for What Really Matters''''' is a memoir written by [[Chesley Sullenberger]] and [[Jeffrey Zaslow]] (1958–2012) describing the events of [[US Airways Flight 1549]]. The ''[[New York Times]]'' bestselling autobiography of [[Chesley Sullenberger|Capt. Chesley “Sully” Sullenberger]]—the pilot who landed a crippled airplane in New York's [[Hudson River]], saving the lives of the 155 passengers—discusses leadership, responsibility, and service, along with his life story.<ref name=kirjasto>{{cite web |url=https://www.harpercollins.com/9780061924699/highest-duty |title=Highest Duty: My Search for What Really Matters. About the Book |publisher=[[HarperCollins]]}}</ref>
[[Clint Eastwood]] directed a [[Sully (film)|2016 film adaptation]] that received positive reviews from critics.
